TREASURY CHAMBER19 May 1916.  Any reply to this letter should be addressed to - The Secretary, Treasury, Whitehall, London, S.W. and the following number quoted 12672/16 Sir, I have laid before the Lords Commissioners of His Majesty's Treasury your letter of the 12th instant (7924), relative to a claim for £15. 12s. 6d made by the London and North Western Railway Company in respect of the fares of seven members of the party which accompanied Mr. Birrell to Ireland on the 26th ultimo. In reply I am to state that my Lords understand that the arrangements for the journey were made by the News Department of the Foreign Office, which has defrayed the other expenses of the party, and in the circumstances They would suggest that the Railway Company's account should be transmitted to the Foreign Office for settlement. I am, Sir, Your obedient Servant  T.L.Heath  The Ubder Secretary, Dublin Castle<note(I) Repl For copies of letter of 9th inst. from Command Pay Office & enclosure; also of this T.L. (II) Send copies to F.Office TLH</note> <note>(i) Done JB 22/5 (II) Done JB 24/5 (II) despd Nai 24/5</note> 
